cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a new neural network activation function that aims to improve performance and convergence rate. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). However, given the focus on neural networks and optimization, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of MNIST classification and auto-encoder also suggests a focus on computer vision and pattern recognition, which further supports the inclusion of cs.CV as a likely sub-category. The use of natural language processing techniques is not mentioned, so cs.CL is the least likely sub-category.
